The Youths and Students of Mamudo Constituency of Potiskum Local Government Area of Yobe State have unanimously agreed to endorse a retired Director of Land and indigene, Alhaji Aminu Alhaji to contest for the state house of assembly in Mamudo Constituency come 2023 general elections. In his address at the occasion today held at Mamudo Central Primary School, the Chairman of the Youth and Students of Mamudo Constituency, Haruna A.T Farafara said that after due consultation, consideration and Constituency wide sampling of opinions among the youth groups and students, “it came to a conclusion that Alhaji Aminu Alhaji is a well-liked, widely respected and highly acceptable figure to the people”. “Considering the current Predicament and challenges born out of Lack of Concern for the demands of the electorate in this Constituency and looking at past records the remarkable achievements, personal efforts and show of concern to all and sundry displayed by Alhaji Aminu Alhaji, the group, therefore, are firmly confident about his capacity to address all the challenges the constituency is currently facing”. According to him”Mamudo constituency, if Alhaji Aminu Alhaji is given the chance and mandate to serve in the capacity of member state house of assembly Potiskum East, he will serve better”. He added that”Alhaji Aminu Alhaji is eligible to contest for the seat because he is the best qualified for the job.My people this is a call for a better change for good future”. Also speaking, one of the community members, Mohammed Salisu revealed that Mamudo town is lacking adequate power supply voltage” because we are all living on a single transformer, the load is too much on the transformer, we need additional transformers. On his part, Malam Garin Bingel said they are in dire need of a proper representative in the area due to the neglect of the area “we don’t have a health facility, our Primary School is not fenced and neglected, we’re sure that electing Alhaji Aminu Alhaji as member representing Mamudo Constituency will bring more developments”. The occasion attracted important personalities, politicians, Youth and Women organizations among others.